                            <comment id="66917" author="jhammond" created="Wed, 18 Sep 2013 14:23:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch landed to master.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="65525" author="spimpale" created="Mon, 2 Sep 2013 07:26:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I have added a fix for the incorrect return value bug.&lt;br/&gt;
The patch is here --&amp;gt; &lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/7522/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/7522/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="64736" author="jhammond" created="Wed, 21 Aug 2013 15:20:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;On this is addressed, there is the issue that ptlrpcd_addref() increments ptlrpc_users regardless of whether ptlrpcd_init() succeeded.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Also what is the point of calling ptlrpcd_addref() from the obd_setup() methods? ptlrpcd_addref() and hence ptlrpcd_init() is already called from ptlrpc_init(). All of the OBD modules depend on ptlrpc anyway. Is this for liblustre? Can all of theses ptlrcpd_addref() calls just be removed?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
